INSTALL JAVA
------------

  # install openjdk
  yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk
  yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk-devel
  yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk-src
  yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk-demo
  yum install ant
      Ant is a Java-based build tool created as part of the Apache open-source project. 
      You can think of it as a Java version of make. Ant scripts have a structure and 
      are written in XML. Similar to make, Ant targets can depend on other targets

  # make symlink to jdk
  cd ~/java
  ln -s /usr/lib/jvm/java jdk

  # expand src.zip  (this came from yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk-src)
  mkdir jdk/src
  cd jdk/src
  jar xvf ../src.zip

  # download oracle documentation, and unzip
  http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/documentation/java-se-7-doc-download-435117.html
      download jdk-7u65-apidocs.zip
  unzip ~/Downloads/jdk-7u65-apidocs.zip
  mv docs oracle_docs

  # viewing oracle documentation
  file:///home/haid/java/oracle_docs/index.html

  # jdk directories
  bin      - compiler and tools
  demo     - demos
  docs     - html docs
  include  - files for compiling natvie methods
  jre      - java runtime environment
  jre-abrt - ???
  lib      - library files
  sample   - sample (comes with demos)
  src      - library source
  tapset   - ???

  -----------

  # download Core Java Book sample code
  http://horstmann.com/corejava.html
  - download corejave.zip
  - mkdir core_java_book
  - cd core_java_book
  - jar xvf corejava.zip


HELLO WORLD PROGRAM
-------------------

  java hello world program - HelloWorld.java ...
     public class HelloWorld {
         public static void main(String[] args) {
             System.out.println("Hello, World");
             System.out.println(args[0]);
         }
     }

  compile and run
    javac HelloWorld.java
    java HelloWorld


TOOLS
-----

javac  prog.java    # compiles to prog.class
java   prog         # runs prog.class

java   applet.jave 
appletviewer applet.html
